.TH PXCLSQ "1" "January 2025" "pxclsq 1.3.2" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
pxclsq \- manual page for pxclsq 1.3.2
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B pxclsq
[\fI\,OPTIONS\/\fR]...
.SH DESCRIPTION
Clean alignments by removing positions/taxa with too much ambiguous data.
NOTE: proportion/count args are in terms of VALID states, not ambiguous states.
This will take fasta, fastq, phylip, and nexus formats from a file or STDIN.
Results are written in fasta format.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-s\fR, \fB\-\-seqf\fR=\fI\,FILE\/\fR
input sequence file, STDIN otherwise
.TP
\fB\-p\fR, \fB\-\-prop\fR=\fI\,DOUBLE\/\fR
proportion of valid character states required to be present, default=0.5
.TP
\fB\-e\fR, \fB\-\-empty\fR
remove columns that are completely empty (\- or ?)
.TP
\fB\-m\fR, \fB\-\-min\fR=\fI\,INT\/\fR
the minimum number of valid character states required per site
\- a min of 1 is equivalent to \fB\-e\fR above
.TP
\fB\-t\fR, \fB\-\-taxa\fR
consider missing data per taxon (default: per site)
.TP
\fB\-c\fR, \fB\-\-codon\fR
examine sequences by codon rather than site
\- requires all sequences be in frame and of correct length
.TP
\fB\-i\fR, \fB\-\-info\fR
report counts of missing data and exit
\- combine with \fB\-t\fR to get report by taxon (rather than site)
\- combine with \fB\-c\fR to use codons as units
.TP
\fB\-v\fR, \fB\-\-verbose\fR
more verbose output (i.e. if entire seqs are removed)
.TP
\fB\-o\fR, \fB\-\-outf\fR=\fI\,FILE\/\fR
output fasta file, STOUT otherwise
.TP
\fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-help\fR
display this help and exit
.TP
\fB\-V\fR, \fB\-\-version\fR
display version and exit
.TP
\fB\-C\fR, \fB\-\-citation\fR
display phyx citation and exit
.SH CITATION
Brown, Joseph W., Joseph F. Walker, and Stephen A. Smith. 2017. Phyx: phylogenetic tools for unix. Bioinformatics 33(12): 1886-1888. https://doi.org/10.1093/bioinformatics/btx063.
